<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861230-0090 </DOCNO><HL> American Financial RaisesIts Stake in Taft to 14.3%</HL><DD> 12/30/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AFINP TFBTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Financial Corp. and its chairman, Carl H. Lindner, said in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing that they raised their stake in Taft Broadcasting Co. to 14.3% from 13.1%.    In the filing, American Financial, a Cincinnati-based financial-services company, and Mr. Lindner said they control 1,319,850 Taft common shares, including 107,650 purchased from Dec. 8 through Dec. 19 at $112.22 to $115.10 each. According to the filing, American Financial and Mr. Lindner hold the stock for investment purposes, but may change their plans &quot;depending on future developments.&quot;    A Taft spokesman said the Cincinnati-based broadcasting and entertainment concern wouldn't have any comment. </TEXT></DOC>